   diverts the call into the btype==2 pipeline, where ZopfliBlockSplit's replaced
   precondition (inend < 10) is violated by a large inend.  The btype dispatch
   mutants on the inner btype==2 statements are dead in this regime (that path is
   never taken in the original), so they survive -- this is a depth-200 vacuity
   driver and the inner-path mutants are inherently unkillable from btype==0. */
